nly available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die <code><strong>Math.LOG2E</strong></code> Eigenschaft repräsentiert den Logarithmus zur Basis 2 von e, was gerundet 1,443 ist:</p>\n\n<p><math display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mstyle mathvariant=\"monospace\"><mi>Math.LOG2E</mi></mstyle><mo>=</mo><msub><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">log</mo><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>e</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≈</mo><mn>1,442</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"TeX\">\\mathtt{\\mi{Math.LOG2E}} = \\log_2(e) \\approx 1,442</annotation></semantics></math></p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/math-log2e.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"sect3\"><table class=\"standard-table\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th class=\"header\" colspan=\"2\">Eigenschaftsattribute von <code>Math.LOG2E</code></th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Schreibbar</td>\n      <td>nein</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Aufzählbar</td>\n      <td>nein</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Konfigurierbar</td>\n      <td>nein</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Weil <code>LOG2E</code> eine statische Eigenschaft von <code>Math</code> ist, kann diese immer über <code>Math.LOG2E</code> erreicht werden, ohne dass ein Objekt erstellt werden muss (<code>Math</code> ist kein Konstruktor).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_math.log2e","title":"Einsatz von <code>Math.LOG2E</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Die folgende Funktion gibt den Logarithmus zur Basis 2 von <em>e</em> zurück.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush:js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">getLog2e</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">LOG2E</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">getLog2e</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 1.4426950408889634</span></code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von Math.LOG2E"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.0.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.8.1.4\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.LOG2E' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-math.log2e\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.LOG2E' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-math.log2e\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.LOG2E' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Math.LOG2E","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/LOG2E/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/exp\"><code>Math.exp()</code></a></li>\n <li><